nies list contents  history  merger with vodafone in the netherlands  horizon tv  operations  markets  americas  europe  references  external links historyedit liberty global inc was founded in  when liberty media international inc lmi and unitedglobalcom inc ugc merged lmi and ugc became subsidiaries of liberty global the new entity had operations in  countries and networks over approximately  million homes making it one of the largest broadband services companies in the world liberty acquired german company unitymedia in november  for  billion unitymedia was libertys first german acquisition and the largest privateequity exit in europe in  in  liberty sold its stake in jupiter telecommunications a japanese telecommunicationsservices provider as liberty shifted its resources back toward europe in january  liberty global raised its stake in belgiumbased telenet from  to  in june  liberty global acquired british cable group virgin media for  billion in cash and stock the agreement expanded liberty into europes largest cable market the acquisition was ranked as one of the  largest cable deals of all time liberty agreed on october  to sell chellomedia for  billion except for its benelux unit to amc networks it was reported that this acquisition would make liberty global the largest broadband company in the world liberty global announced it would be acquiring dutch cable company ziggo for € billion in january  the acquisition was completed in november  when the services of upc nederland began to be merged into the new business liberty global and discovery communications became joint owners of allmedia in may  in a £ million joint deal in july  liberty global acquired a  stake in itv plc valued at £ million libertys stake in the company increased to  in july  in november  liberty global announced its acquisition of cable  wireless communications the  billion deal expanded liberty globals presence into the caribbean  greater latin america the acquisition was completed in may  in  liberty established the stock liberty latin american  caribbean lilac focusing on panama and the caribbean with assets in chile and puerto rico liberty global is also owner of cable  wireless communications seychelles business named cable and wireless seychelles a vestige of cwcs once expansive portfolio which once included businesses in macau monaco monaco telecom jersey isle of man guernsey st helena ascension island falkland islands and diego garcia under the brand sure sold to batelco the company also currently owns a  stake in majority stateowned trinidadian telco tstt which it has been obliged to dispose of which competes with their wholly owned subsidiary flow trinidad liberty global paid approximately  million for a  stake in lions gate entertainment group in november  liberty ceo mike fries joined the lions gate board of directors as part of the acquisition liberty invested £million in global broadband cable network technetix in july  in november  liberty globals virgin media subsidiary released its netflix and other appenabled settop v box merger with vodafone in the netherlandsedit in june  vodafone confirmed talks with liberty global focused on potential partnerships but denied that a full merger was in the works liberty global invested in guavus a data analytics company in september  in february  it was announced that vodafone and liberty global would merge dutch operations libertys dutch subsidiary ziggo would work with vodafones mobile network vodafone paid liberty € billion as part of the joint venture valued at € billion the deal was approved by the european commission in august  on december   the proposed merger of liberty globals and vodafone groups dutch operations was completed resulting in a joint venture called vodafoneziggo group holding bv horizon tvedit horizon tv is liberty globals flagship platform with more than  million firstgeneration horizon tv devices sold liberty global launched horizon tv a box to stream to tvs in  h an upgraded version of the horizon box was launched in  the new system included an upgraded remote control with a qwerty keyboard a secondary box connects wirelessly to the main device allowing tv dvr and vod streaming to multiple rooms in a subscribers house liberty partnered with activevideo in  to include activevideos cloudtv on the horizon boxes twitter was integrated into horizons mobile app library in  the addition allowed live tweets to be overlaid onto the screen of a program being broadcast also in  horizon tv was launched in austria making it available in all three germanspeaking countries that liberty global operates in operationsedit liberty global operates through the following subsidiaries allmedia  ownership with discovery communications itv plc united kingdom  shareholding lionsgate  ownership with discovery communications john c malone att and mark rachesky telenet belgium  ownership base upc broadband upc austria upc czech republic upc magyarország hungary upc polska poland upc romania upc slovakia upc switzerland efon  ownership upc dth upc direct hungary freesat czech republic and slovakia focus sat romania unitymedia germany virgin media virgin mobile uk united kingdom virgin media ireland republic of ireland tv group virgin mobile ireland vodafoneziggo  ownership vodafone netherlands ziggo ziggo sport ziggo sport totaal marketsedit americasedit part of liberty global is separately listed as lilac liberty latin america and caribbean group operating in over  countries under the consumer brands vtr flow liberty más móvil and btc as well as having a subsea fiber network liberty globals operations in the americas consists of liberty puerto rico a provider of pay tv internet and telephone services in puerto rico and vtr a chilean cable provider of television telephone mobile and internet services through the acquisition of cable and wireless communications liberty global has become the owner of the largest paytv and broadband provider in the caribbean in addition the company also owns cwcs operations in the seychelles named cable and wireless seychelles europeedit liberty global serves  countries in europe and is among the largest cable operators in austria belgium the czech republic hungary romania ireland the netherlands poland slovakia switzerland and the united kingdom referencesedit  a b c d tamara chuang may   liberty global doesnt make money in denver but moved its headquarters here heres why the denver post retrieved september     a b c d financials yahoo finances   peeringdb   a b liberty global to buy virgin media for bn bbc news february   retrieved february     mari silbey february   liberty global presses pause on k wifi first hopes light reading retrieved september     liberty global reports q and h  results pdf liberty global august   retrieved september      liberty global forbes retrieved february     time richardson june   liberty ugc complete merger the register retrieved september     amy bryer january   liberty media international unitedglobal merge denver business journal retrieved september     liberty global to buy unitymedia for  billion the new york times november   retrieved september     jeffrey mccraken daisuke wakabayahi january   liberty global to sell stake in jupiter the wall street journal retrieved september     a b tartaglione nancy october   amc networks to pay b for liberty global’s chellomedia deadlinecom accessed on october    dana cimilluca lilly vitorovich anupreeta das feb   liberty global to acquire virgin media the wall street journal retrieved september     juliette garside february   virgin media bought for £bn by liberty global the guardian retrieved september     mark scott eric pfanner february   liberty global reaches deal for virgin media the new york times retrieved september     briel robert january   liberty global to acquire ziggo for €bn broadband tv news retrieved january     mark sweney may   allmedia sold to discovery and liberty global in deal worth £m the